ance itself in this pivotal period, one that transcends the binary framework through which we too often view history by revealing the deep roots of exchange between Europe and the Muslim world, and showing how Arab France was in fact integral to the dawn of modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAsianistszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aIslam and politics. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh  a19th century.  aanthropology.  aarab france.  aarab world.  aarchives.  acolonial expansion.  acolonialism.  aegyptians.  aengaging.  aeuropean history.  aeuropean muslims.  aeuropean scholars.  afrance.  afranco arab authors.  afrench army.  afrench empire.  agreeks.  ahistorians.  ahistorical record.  ahistory buffs.  aislam.  amodern europe.  amodern history.  amodernity.  amuslim history.  amuslim world.  amuslims.  anapoleonic occupation.  anonfiction.  apolitical.  aretrospective.  arevolutions.  asyrians.  awars.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026065840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094754240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947542423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947542/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY